<paragraph id="A23B8905FF92FFB50CEAFDBDFCDAFD1A" blockId="2.[151,1436,601,700]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
This is the single species of the genus found outside the Neotropical region. Together with 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF92FFB508E6FDBDFF65FD3E" authority="Nagy, 1975" authorityName="Nagy" authorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Ycaploca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB508E6FDBDFAE4FDD5" box="[1179,1363,601,627]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Ycaploca evansi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C615F4F4FF92FFB50927FDBEFF65FD3E" author="Nagy, C. G." pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="75 - 78" refId="ref7117" refString="Nagy, C. G. (1975) A new genus of Scolebythidae (Hymenoptera) from South Africa and Australia. Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 38 (1), 75 - 78." type="journal article" year="1975">Nagy, 1975</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, they are the only species of 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF92FFB50E6EFD99FD05FD31" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1963" box="[531,690,637,663]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scolebythidae</taxonomicName>
recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="DA93C995FF92FFB50F46FD99FC12FD31" box="[827,933,637,663]" name="Australia" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Australia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF92FFB50FD2FD9AFBE7FD31" authorityName="Lepeco &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2021" box="[943,1104,637,664]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australiana">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB50FD2FD9AFBE7FD31" box="[943,1104,637,664]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">C. australiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="7D3F37A7FF92FFB5091CFD99FF70FD1A" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen, which was collected over one hundred years ago.
</paragraph>
